{"sectionId":741,"sectionIdLiteral":"741","humanId":"lesson-320","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"My Father gives all power unto me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 320"},"annotation":"W-320","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-320\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"741#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>The Son of God is limitless.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>There are no limits on his strength, his peace, his joy, nor any attributes his Father gave in his creation.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>What he wills with his Creator and Redeemer must be done.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>His holy will can never be denied, because his Father shines upon his mind, and lays before it all the strength and love in earth and Heaven.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>I am he to whom all this is given.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>I am he in whom the power of my Father‚Äôs Will abides.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"741#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Your Will can do all things in me, and then extend to all the world as well through me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>There is no limit on Your Will.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"741#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>And so all power has been given to Your Son.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"The Son of God is limitless. There are no limits on his strength, his peace, his joy, nor any attributes his Father gave in his creation. What he wills with his Creator and Redeemer must be done. His","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 320: My Father gives all power unto me |